-- HK shares close down 0.5 pct, AgBank eases ahead of results
-- 
-- Tue Mar 25, 2014 04:07AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, March 25 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares ended down on Tuesday, as investors locked in recent gains ahead of earnings results from Chinese banks later this week, with the index dragged down by heavyweight Tencent.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed down 0.5 percent at 21,732.32. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the top Chinese listings in Hong Kong closed flat. Agricultural Bank of China <1288.HK> slid 0.3 percent ahead of its earnings due later on Tuesday. Sinopharm Group <1099.HK>, China's largest pharmaceutical distributor, gained 2.2 percent after Credit Suisse upgraded it to outperform from neutral. The brokerage said the firm's core earnings growth may gradually improve in 2015-16. Tencent <0700.HK> fell 4.9 percent after it hit an eight-day high on Monday.